sentences.english: If a man pampers his servant from youth, he will bring grief in the end.
sentences.chinese: 人將僕人從小嬌養，這僕人終久必成了他的兒子。

sentences.english: Listen to advice and accept instruction, and in the end you will be wise.
sentences.chinese: 你要聽勸教，受訓誨，使你終久有智慧。

sentences.english: He that delicately bringeth up his servant from a child shall have him become his son at the length.
sentences.chinese: 人將僕人從小嬌養，這僕人終久必成了他的兒子。

sentences.english: Hear counsel, and receive instruction, that thou mayest be wise in thy latter end.
sentences.chinese: 你要聽勸教，受訓誨，使你終久有智慧。

sentences.english: Do you not know that the end will be bitter?
sentences.chinese: 你豈不知終久必有苦楚嗎？

sentences.english: We often do not see through things, and never can be done.
sentences.chinese: 我們常常不能看透的事，終久可以做到。

sentences.english: Though thy beginning was small, yet thy latter end should greatly increase.
sentences.chinese: 你起初雖然微小，終久必甚發達。
